With the exception of this latter, all the formularies are arranged in the order followed in the Gallican Mass, but many among them, especially the Messes in honour of saints, are Roman formularies.

This Missal contains a Mass in honour cf St. Leger, in which his relies are spoken cf as being distributed through· out Gaul. St. Leger, Bishop of Autan, died in 680. The manuscript cannot therefore be earlier than the final years of the seventh century. In Mons. Delisle’s opinion, its data should not be placed later than tha beginning of the following century.
